@IAMJES Then two questions:
1) does the 192.168.1.0/24 network on eth0 have a router (should be the ‘gateway’ IP device) that does NAT? 192.168.x.x addresses aren’t routable on the Internet 
2) Is the DRP node acting as the router between the nodes network (192.168.0.0/24 in your example above) and the Internet-connected network (192.168.1.0/24 in your example above) ?
